{"PageNumber":7,"Angle":0,"RotatedAngle":0,"Height":1620,"Width":2880,"OriginHeight":0,"OriginWidth":0,"Elements":[{"Index":0,"Type":"title","Text":"#  Elgamal cryptosystem","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":214,"Y":305},"LeftTop":{"X":214,"Y":179},"RightBottom":{"X":1357,"Y":305},"RightTop":{"X":1357,"Y":179}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":1,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● The security of this scheme is based on the fact that, without knowing x, it would be very difficult for an eavesdropper to decrypt the ciphertext, (a, b)","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":214,"Y":636},"LeftTop":{"X":214,"Y":427},"RightBottom":{"X":2555,"Y":636},"RightTop":{"X":2555,"Y":427}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":2,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Since everyone knows $y = \\textcircled{21} \\mod p$, from Bob's public key, the security of this scheme is therefore related to the difficulty of solving the discrete logarithm problem","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":214,"Y":862},"LeftTop":{"X":214,"Y":655},"RightBottom":{"X":2584,"Y":862},"RightTop":{"X":2584,"Y":655}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":3,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● That is, Elgamal could be broken by an eavesdropper finding the secret key, x","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":214,"Y":1023},"LeftTop":{"X":214,"Y":882},"RightBottom":{"X":2503,"Y":1023},"RightTop":{"X":2503,"Y":882}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":4,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● This can be only done by solving the discrete logarithm problem which is believed to computationally hard","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":320,"Y":1149},"LeftTop":{"X":320,"Y":1023},"RightBottom":{"X":2558,"Y":1149},"RightTop":{"X":2558,"Y":1023}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":5,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Note that an Elgamal encryption is dependent on the choice of the random number, $k$","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":214,"Y":1306},"LeftTop":{"X":214,"Y":1169},"RightBottom":{"X":2379,"Y":1306},"RightTop":{"X":2379,"Y":1169}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":6,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Different k should be chosen for different message encryption","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":320,"Y":1382},"LeftTop":{"X":320,"Y":1311},"RightBottom":{"X":2040,"Y":1382},"RightTop":{"X":2040,"Y":1311}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":7,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● If k is reused she would be leaking information much like the one-time pad would leak information if we were to reuse a pad","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":214,"Y":1543},"LeftTop":{"X":214,"Y":1399},"RightBottom":{"X":2495,"Y":1543},"RightTop":{"X":2495,"Y":1399}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""}]}